@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Gruer's Story";
}

<div class="container my-5">
    <div class="row justify-content-center">
        <div class="col-lg-8">

            <!-- HERO -->
            <div class="warm-card text-center mb-5">
                <i class="bi bi-egg-fried display-1 text-warm"></i>

                <h1 class="display-4 mt-3 brand-baked">
                    Gruer’s Story
                </h1>

                <p class="text-muted mt-2">
                    A dream, spoken by the man who baked it into existence.
                </p>

                <div class="honey-accent mx-auto"></div>
            </div>

            <!-- STORY -->
            <div class="warm-card">

                <div class="story-text">

                    <p class="lead fst-italic">
                        “You want to hear my dream, signore?”
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        I close my eyes sometimes… just to feel it again.
                        The smell of warm bread. The sound of ovens breathing.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        I see it clearly now.
                        Not as memory… but as something waiting to exist.
                    </p>

                    <p class="fst-italic">
                        “A shop… but not just a shop.”
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        Warm wood under your hands.
                        Stone that holds the heat of the day.
                        Light that does not blind you — it welcomes you.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        And the ovens…
                        Ah, the ovens.
                        I want them visible.
                        No secrets.
                        Let people see the fire that creates what they eat.
                    </p>

                    <div class="honey-accent my-4"></div>

                    <p class="fst-italic text-center">
                        “Because bread is not made in silence… it is made in truth.”
                    </p>

                    <div class="honey-accent my-4"></div>

                    <p>
                        But there is more… always more.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        Light that feels almost impossible.
                        Gold… amber… soft as morning honey.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        Plants that do not belong anywhere I know —
                        yet somehow feel like they have always been there.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        A place that feels like home…
                        but also like somewhere you have never been before.
                    </p>

                    <p class="fst-italic">
                        “That is what I want, signore. Not perfection. Feeling.”
                    </p>

                    <div class="honey-accent my-4"></div>

                    <p>
                        Behind the counter… dark wood.
                        Solid. Honest.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        Behind it… the ovens.
                        Alive. Honest.
                        Burning gently like a heartbeat.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        And the pastries…
                        not just food…
                        but small stories you can hold in your hands.
                    </p>

                    <p class="lead fst-italic text-center mt-4">
                        “If I can make someone feel something when they take a bite… then I have done my job.”
                    </p>

                    <p class="text-end mt-4">
                        — Gruer
                    </p>

                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
    </div>
</div>